JetBrains Mono
==============

Source:  https://www.jetbrains.com/lp/mono/
Repo:    https://github.com/JetBrains/JetBrainsMono
License: SIL Open Font License 1.1 (see LICENSE)

The .ttf files in this directory are vendored from the upstream
JetBrains Mono project (Copyright 2020 The JetBrains Mono Project Authors).

Vendored on:     2026-05-14
Vendored files:
  - JetBrainsMono-Regular.ttf   (weight 400)
  - JetBrainsMono-Medium.ttf    (weight 500 — the weight used by the
                                 .numeric-display / .numeric-value /
                                 .numeric-caption classes per UI Design
                                 Book §3.2 and story 266)
  - JetBrainsMono-Bold.ttf      (weight 700)

Per UI Design Book §3.2 (Typography), JetBrains Mono is the preferred
member of the `-font-mono` token's family stack:

    -font-mono: "JetBrains Mono", "IBM Plex Mono", "Cascadia Code",
                "Consolas", monospace;

It is the lead family in the stack because:

  - true tabular figures (every digit is the same width — column 1 of
    `09:59:59.9` lines up with column 1 of `10:00:00.0`, eliminating the
    "time-display flicker" that proportional fonts cause);
  - weight 500 ("Medium") matches the prescribed weight for numeric
    readouts in §3.2;
  - SIL OFL 1.1 license — same liberal terms as the Lucide ISC license
    we already vendor (free to ship, free to fork, source-revision
    tracked here).

Loading
-------

The fonts are registered with the JavaFX font system at application
startup by `DawApplication.loadBundledFonts()`. If `Font.loadFont(...)`
fails (platform-specific font subsystem unavailable, file missing,
corrupt), the call is logged at WARNING and the app continues — the
CSS stack falls back to IBM Plex Mono / Cascadia Code / Consolas /
monospace in order.

Adding or updating a weight
---------------------------

1. Download the .ttf from
   https://github.com/JetBrains/JetBrainsMono/raw/master/fonts/ttf/JetBrainsMono-$WEIGHT.ttf
   (or the matching tagged release) into this directory.
2. Add the resource path to the `resources` array in
   `DawApplication.loadBundledFonts()`.
3. Update the vendored-files list above with the new weight.
4. `FontResourcesTest` will pick up the family if `Font.loadFont` accepts
   it; the test logs a warning rather than failing if loading is skipped
   (headless CI on a host without a font subsystem).
